<p>Philosophers at  <a href="https://cssh.northeastern.edu/philosophy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Northeastern University</a> have been awarded two substantial grants for work related to artificial intelligence.<span id="more-55934"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-55935 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/creel-k-basl-j-1024x581.png" alt="" width="723" height="410" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/creel-k-basl-j-1024x581.png 1024w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/creel-k-basl-j-300x170.png 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/creel-k-basl-j-768x436.png 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/creel-k-basl-j-400x227.png 400w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/creel-k-basl-j.png 1436w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 723px) 100vw, 723px" /></p>
<p>One is a $400,000 grant to <a href="https://kathleenacreel.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Katie Creel</a> and <a href="https://johnbasl.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">John Basl</a> from the <a href="https://sloan.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Alfred P. Sloan Foundation</a>, for the project &#8220;Cultivating Robust AI and Society Research Capacity and Community&#8221;.</p>
<p>This award will support the <a href="http://www.aidesummer.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AI + Data Ethics (AIDE) Summer Graduate Training Program</a> as well as a summer field school that brings together Sloan Foundation <a href="https://sloan.org/programs/digital-technology/exploratory-grantmaking-in-technology/metascience-ai-postdoctoral-fellowships" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Metascience &amp; AI Postdoctoral Fellows</a>, the Computing Research Association&#8217;s <a href="https://cra.org/cra-trustworthy-ai-research-fellowship/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">&#8220;Trustworthy AI&#8221; Fellows</a>, and participants in the AIDE Summer program to develop interdisciplinary research capacities across epistemological, scientific, social and ethical issues raised by AI.</p>
<p>The other grant, for $1.47 million, is from the US <a href="https://www.nsf.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">National Science Foundation</a>. It is an Industry-University Cooperative Research Center Grant to launch the <a href="https://moritzlaw.osu.edu/CRAIG" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Center for Responsible AI and Governance</a> (CRAIG), a multi-institution project that aims to bring together industry partners and academic researchers to identify and solve technical and governance challenges in the space of responsible AI.  John <span class="il">Basl</span> (philosophy) is the PI for the Northeastern University site.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/12/12/two-substantial-ai-related-grants-for-northeastern-university-philosophers/">Two Substantial AI-Related Grants for Northeastern University Philosophers</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>